  "analysis": {
    "domain_shift": "The model was trained on 131K Polaris production logs labeled by Drishti heuristics. In that dataset, 54% of traces are labeled healthy, and rare dimensions like interface_choice (1.2%), file_strategy (1.4%), parallelism_efficiency (1.6%) have very low prevalence. TraceBench traces are specifically designed/curated to exhibit issues, creating a severe prior mismatch.",
    "parse_failures": "7/35 traces (all IO500 subset: ior-hard, ior-rnd, mdtest) failed to parse due to incompatible darshan log format (unable to inflate). These traces used a different darshan version than our parser supports.",
    "key_findings": [
      "Model predicts healthy/empty for 24/28 parsed traces, reflecting the strong healthy prior from training data",
      "Only parallelism_efficiency gets any correct predictions (4/18 recall), likely because it corresponds to a Drishti heuristic that triggered on benchmark-like workloads",
      "access_granularity (12 true positives in GT) gets 0 predictions, suggesting the model learned different thresholds for small I/O from production data vs benchmark criteria",
      "interface_choice (21 true positives) gets 0 predictions - this label (NC-R/NC-W/LLL/MPNM) is very rare in Drishti-labeled production data",
      "file_strategy (14 true positives) gets 0 predictions - shared file access labeled differently between Drishti heuristics and TraceBench criteria"
    ],
    "comparison_notes": "IOAgent (IPDPS 2025) reports 0.641 exact-match accuracy on TraceBench using an LLM-based approach with access to raw darshan-parser output. Our ML approach gets 0.036 exact-match. The gap is expected because: (1) IOAgent uses text-based reasoning that can adapt to new labeling criteria, (2) our model learned Polaris-specific patterns from Drishti heuristics, (3) TraceBench uses different labeling criteria than Drishti.",
    "implications": "This result highlights the domain adaptation challenge: an ML model trained on heuristic labels from one system does not generalize to external benchmarks with different labeling criteria. This motivates our LLM component (Track B) which can bridge the gap through reasoning."
  }
}